President Obama has announced his intent to nominate Victoria A. Lipnic for the position of Commissioner of the Equal Employment Opportunity Commission (EEOC). Lipnic has been serving as a Commissioner of the EEOC since 2010. Prior to joining the EEOC, she worked as Of Counsel to Seyfarth Shaw LLP and served as the Assistant Secretary of Labor for Employment Standards at the Department of Labor from 2002 to 2009. She also worked as Workforce Policy Counsel on the Education and Labor Committee in the United States House of Representatives. Lipnic has a background in labor and employment matters, having worked as in-house counsel for the United States Postal Service and as a Special Assistant for Business Liaison to former Secretary of Commerce Malcolm Baldrige. She holds a B.A. from Allegheny College and a J.D. from George Mason University School of Law.